chos mngon pa|Skt abhidharma, abhidharmaḥ\nEN Abhidharma, metaphysics, phenomenology — The third section of the Tripitaka (the other two sections being the Vinaya and the Sutras). The Abhidharma is the corpus of texts expounding the metaphysical content of the Sutras. [in Jigme Lingpa & Kangyur R. "Treasury of Precious Qualities" Vol.1, Padmakara, Shambhala, Boston, 2004.] One of the three pitakas. The foundation of Buddhist psychology and logic. It describes the universe, the different kinds of beings, the steps on the path to enlightenment, refutes mistaken beliefs, etc. [WOMPT, 1998] One of the three baskets; the branch of the Buddha’s teachings that deals mainly with psychology and logic. [TLWF, 2011][NS] One of the Three Pitakas; the branch of the Buddha’s teachings that deals mainly with psychology and logic. [NLF, 2005] [ZT, 2006] The third part of the Tripitaka, the "three baskets." The Abhidharma is the corpus of texts expounding Buddhist metaphysical teaching. [LLB, 2002] One of the three scriptural collections; the branch of the Buddha’s teachings that deals mainly with psychology and logic. [OMS, 2018]\nFR Abhidharma — l'un des trois recueils du canon bouddhiste (Tripitaka ou Triple Corbeille) ; éclairant et développant les enseignements des soûtras, il décrit l'univers, les êtres, les étapes de la voie de l'Éveil, etc., en réfutant les opinions erronées. [POL, 1999] La Connaissance non souillée et son entourage, la connaissance née de l'étude et de la réflexion, ainsi que les paroles du Bouddha et leurs commentaires qui forment la Corbeille consacrée à l'entraînement à la connaissance supérieure. [TDPQ, 2009] Les paroles du Bouddha et les traités qui forment la Corbeille consacrée à l’entraînement à la connaissance supérieure. [CC, Glossaire Dalaï Lama]\nPT Abhidharma — A terceira secção do Tripiṭaka – sendo as outras duas as secções do Vinaya e dos Sūtras. O Abhidharma é o conjunto dos ensinamentos do Buda relativos à análise e classificação dos fenóme