chos rgyal 'phags pa|EN Chögyal Pakpa — (1235-1280), one of the five great scholars of the Sakya school known as the Sakya Gongma. He became the preceptor of Mongolian emperor Kublai Khan and regent of Tibet. [WOMPT, 1998] The influential Sakya master Chögyal Pakpa Lodrö Gyaltsen (1235–1280), who was Sakya Pandita’s nephew. As well as being the fifth leader of the Sakya school, he was the spiritual advisor of the Mongol emperor Kublai Khan, and played an important political role in Tibet. [TLWF 2011]\nFR Cheugyel Pakpa — (1235-1280), maître sakyapa qui devint précepteur de Kubilaï Khan et régent du Tibet ; cinquième des Sakya Gongma. [CGP, 1997]\nPT Chögyal Phakpa — O influente mestre Sakya Chögyal Pakpa Lodrö Gyaltsen (1235-1280), sobrinho de Sakya Paṇḍita. Além de ser o quinto líder da escola Sakya, ele foi o conselheiro espiritual do imperador mongol Kublai Khan, e desempenhou um papel político importante no Tibete. [TLWF 2011]\nES Chögyal Phakpa — (1235-1280), uno de los cinco grandes eruditos de la escuela Sakya conocido como Sakya Gongma. Fue el preceptor del emperador mongol Kublai Khan y regente de Tíbet.[PMP, 2002]\nIT Chögyal Pakpa — 1235-1280, uno dei cinque grandi eruditi della scuola Sakyapa conosciuto come il Sakya Gongma. Divenne il precettore dell’imperatore mongolo Kublai Khan e fu eletto governatore reggente delle province del Tibet.
