rgya gad zer|EN (relatives) scolding you — scolding in the sense of telling you that practicing the Dharma is a waste of time and that you should be doing something more worthwhile.Matthieu said ‘words' in the sense of arguments and quarrels, but the commentary merely talks about advice, etc. [ZT, 2006, translator's notes]
