ri rab|Skt meru , sumeru, meruparvata , sumeruvat, acalendra\nZH 須彌山 (Xūmíshān)\nEN Mount Meru — Immense mountain, wider at the top than at the bottom, around which the four continents of the world are disposed, according to ancient Indian cosmology. The immense mountain, wider at the top than at the bottom, that forms the center of the universe around which the four continents of the world are disposed, according to the ancient Indian cosmology. [TLWF, 2011][OMS, 2018] The name of an immense cosmic mountain, acting as the axis of the universe and around which are located the four continents. Every universal system has its Mount Meru and four continents. [TPQ, 2010] Lit.“the supreme mountain”: the four-sided mountain in the form of an inverted pyramid which is the center of our universe according to Buddhist cosmology. [NLF, 2005][ZT, 2006] The king of mountains and world-axis, according to the cosmology of ancient India. Around it are located the four continents and eight subcontinents, of which one universe is composed. All universes, of which there are an infinite number, are arranged in the same way. [LLB, 2002] See Mount Meru [LLB, 2002] The great mountain at the center of a universal system according to the cosmology of ancient India. [WL, 2012]\nFR Mont Méru, Mont Suprême — Axe d’un monde sur lequel s’étagent des paradis et à la cime duquel se dresse le palais d’Indra, le roi des dieux. [M, 2003] le mont Meru, immense montagne, sorte d’axe du monde autour duquel se répartissent les quatre « continents », selon la cosmologie indienne. [CGP, 1997] axe du monde dans les mythologies indo-bouddhistes. [SEDA, 2019] montagne cosmique faisant figure d'axe du monde et autour de laquelle se trouvent les quatre continents. Chaque monde est doté d'un Mérou, de quatre continents et de huit sous-continents. [TDPQ, 2009]\nPT Monte Meru — Segundo a cosmologia do budista, trata-se de uma imensa montanha cósmica que serve de eixo do universo e em torno da qual estão dispostos os quatro continentes. Cada sistema universal é composto por um Monte Meru e quatro continentes.\nES Monte Meru — Según la cosmología budista, es una inmensa montaña cósmica, más ancha en la cima que en la base, que sirve como eje del universo y alrededor del cual están dispuestos los cuatro continentes. Cada sistema universal consta de un Monte Meru y cuatro continentes.\nIT Monte Meru — Immensa montagna cosmica che funge da asse dell’universo e intorno alla quale sono disposti i quattro continenti. Ogni sistema universale consta di un monte Meru e quattro continenti.
