sems 'khrid|FR introduction à l'esprit* — [G-T]
sems bden|FR isolement de l'esprit* — [GE]
sems bskyed|EN arouse the mind of enlightenment, develop the mind of enlightenment, develop enlightened atitude\nFR cultiver l'esprit d'Eveil, Production de l’esprit d’Éveil — Voir note 143. [CGP, 1997]\nPT cultivar/ desenvolver /gerar a bodhicitta
sems byung|Skt caitta, caitāsika\nEN mental factors — These are innumerable mental factors or events concomitant with the consciousness (the main mind), which can be gath­ered, according to Asanga, in fifty-one principal ones. These are again subdi­vided into six groups: (1) five omnipresent factors; (2) five object-ascertaining factors; (3) eleven wholesome factors; (4) six root defilements; (5) twenty lesser defilements; and (6) four variable factors. [IMW, 2004] The aspects of mental function that accompany the main mind (citta), apprehending and reacting to the objects detected by consciousness.[OMS, 2018]\nFR facteur / événement mental*, facteurs mentaux* — les facteurs mentaux constituent l'une des deux sous-catégories des facteurs de composition, l'autre regroupant les facteurs non coïncidents, lesquels ne peuvent être classés ni avec la matière ni avec l'esprit. Voir Esprit (principal) et Facteur de composition. [TDPQ, 2009] [SPB, 2020][RL, 2010][G-T]\nPT fatores mentais — São inúmeros factores ou eventos mentais concomitantes com a consciência (a mente principal), que podem ser reunidos, segundo Asanga, em cinquenta e um fatores principais. Estes são novamente subdivididos em seis grupos: (1) cinco fatores omnipresentes; (2) cinco fatores que determinam os objetos; (3) onze fatores saudáveis; (4) seis obscurecimentos base; (5) vinte obscurecimentos menores; e (6) quatro fatores variáveis. [IMW 2004].
