srong btsan sgam po|EN Songtsen Gampo — (617-698), 33rd king of Tibet and one of the three great religious kings. It was during his time that the first Buddhist temples were built. [ZT, 2006] The first Buddhist king of Tibet, who flourished in the seventh century and is said to have been a manifestation of the Bodhisattva Avalokiteshvara, or Chenrezig. Four reigns separate him from Trisong Detsen (eighth and ninth centuries) [LLB, 2002]\nFR Songtsen Gampo — (617-698), 33e roi du Tibet, l’un des trois grands rois religieux (avec Thrisong Detsen et Thri Relpachen). C’est durant son règne que furent construits les premiers temples bouddhistes. Voir note 27. [CGP, 1997]\nPT Songtsen Gampo — (617-698), 33º rei do Tibete e um dos três grandes reis religiosos. Foi durante a sua época que os primeiros templos budistas foram construídos.\nES Songtsen Gampo — (617-698) Trigésimo tercer rey del Tíbet y uno de los tres grandes reyes religiosos. Durante su reinado se construyeron los primeros templos budistas en el Tíbet.[PMP, 2014]\nIT Songtsen Gampo — (617-698) Il 33° re del Tibet e uno dei tre grandi re religiosi. I primi templi buddhisti vennero costruiti sotto il suo regno.
